# Epic H — meta-owned toolchain convergence (eliminate system-depth installs).
# Each tool installs into $META_ROOT/.toolchains/<x> and exposes regular frontdoor wrappers in $META_ROOT/usr/bin,
# replacing an apt/system install. See docs/adr-install-locations-and-local-state.md
# (§System-depth convergence plan) and .handoff/loop/backlog.md Epic H.
#
# Install-only by default: components that ALSO change build behavior install the
# binary here. Wiring that changes the global build config is gated behind a build-
# verification step so an apply can never silently break the workspace's own builds.
# wild (the linker) is now FULLY WIRED + verified (Epic H TASK-0054): its install
# writes the meta-root $META_ROOT/.cargo/config.toml linker section and a full
# `cargo build` was confirmed to link via `clang --ld-path=wild` before it landed.
